-- ECB's Bini Says Euro Isn't in Danger, Doesn't See Any Problems for Italy
-- B y   M a r c o   B e r t a c c h e   a n d   A r m o r e l   K e n n a
-- 2010-11-26T06:17:19Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2010-11-26/ecb-s-bini-says-euro-isn-t-in-danger-doesn-t-see-any-problems-for-italy.html
European Central Bank executive
board member Lorenzo Bini Smaghi said the euro isn’t in danger
in an interview with Italy’s RAI television.  “If Italy respects the rigor in public accounts and pushes
through agreed budget measures, it won’t have any problems,”
Bini said in an interview with Italy’s TG2 late yesterday.  To contact the editor responsible for this story:
